oDocs Eye Care is a New Zealand social enterprise. It was founded in 2014 by Dr. Hong Sheng Chiong and Dr. Benjamin O'Keeffe in Wellington, New Zealand. The company sought to improve access to eye care by making affordable smartphone-based ophthalmic imaging devices. Their product, ODocs, was publicly disclosed in 2015 when he delivered the message at TEDxAuckland. In 2015, the company won the New Zealand Health Informatics Clinician challenge for the active project category.
